    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your oven-proof dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces and add them to a large <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your<strong> garlic </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife (but keep the skins on!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish[es] with your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the dish[es] in the oven for an initial 35 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your <strong>dried basil</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>herby stock</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into rounds and set them aside for later</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 35 min, remove the dish[es] from the oven and pour the <strong>herby stock</strong> all over the potatoes and tomatoes</p><p>Top with your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong></p><p>Squeeze over the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and top the fish with the<strong> reserved lemon slices</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the dish[es] to the oven for 15-20 min or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>baked lemon & herb fish with cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Add a few knobs of <strong>butter</strong> to the potatoes and leave to melt</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-lemon-and-herb-cod-with-cherry-tomatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, tear your<strong> parsley & dill </strong>all over the <strong>baked lemon & herb fish with cherry tomatoes </strong>(watch out for the garlic skins!)</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> shredded lettuce</strong> with a little<strong> olive oil</strong> and serve it alongside</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
